article.headline: Portland St. 59, Sacramento St. 42
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. -- Julius Thomas had 10 points and 10 rebounds to lift Portland State to a 59-42 win over Sacramento State on Sunday. Kyle Coston led Portland State (17-7, 8-3 Big Sky) with 11 points. Dominic Waters came off the bench to add nine. Portland State broke open an 8-8 tie midway through the first half with a 24-8 run that gave it a 32-16 lead at the break. The Vikings led by as many as 27 points in the second half and were never challenged as they sent the Hornets to their 35th straight road loss. Loren Leath and Justin Eller led Sacramento State (2-22, 1-10 Big Sky) with 10 points each. Portland State shot 34 percent from the floor and Sacramento State connected on 33 percent. The Vikings, however, made 10 3-pointers while holding the Hornets to 1-of-9 from beyond the arc.
